France's Jean-Baptiste Grange Wins Slalom Title at World Ski Championships

-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 
2011-02-20T15:17:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-20/france-s-jean-baptiste-grange-wins-slalom-title-at-world-ski-championships.html
  France ’s Jean-Baptiste Grange won
the men’s slalom title, the final event of skiing’s  Alpine World
Championships , ahead of  Sweden ’s Jens Byggmark.  Grange, 26, who won a silver medal in the discipline four
years ago, clocked a combined two-leg time of 1 minute, 41.72
seconds in Garmisch-Partenkirchen,  Germany  today, 0.43 second
faster than Byggmark. Manfred Moelgg of  Italy  was third.  France finishes the championships with two gold medals
after taking the team event on Feb. 16. Austria  topped the
standings  with four golds, three silver medals and a bronze.  Grange is currently second in the World Cup slalom
standings, trailing  Croatia ’s Ivica Kostelic, who was only
eighth today.  To contact the reporter on this story:  James Cone  in  London  at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:  Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 